G images in RGBA format with a valid alpha channel.%0a%3c * Per-pixel transparency is supported and you are encouraged to use it.%0a%3c * The images should be as small as possible to avoid performance issues when using a large number of tabs.%0a%3c * The images' overall opacity should be around 50%25. This allows the colorized underlays to be visible so that colorized versions for the active/inactive and hovered tabs are possible.%0a%3c * The images should be grayscale to make colorizing work best. This does not apply to the **unknown.png**.%0a%3c * The margins of the images are internally set to 5 pixels on each side. The inner part of the image will be stretched in both directions, so make sure to not use more than 5 pixels for a margin that should not be stretched.\\\%0a%3c %0a%3c For the glow effect image, you can set the opacity higher to make it appear with some contrast. Depending on your plugin settings, TabSRMM will try to colorize the images with the current Aero theme color (the color you can choose on the Windows desktop under %25class=option%25Personalize->Window color%25%25).\\\%0a%3c %0a%3c === Related reading ===%0a%3c * [[ColorThemes|+]]%0a%3c * [[Aero|Aero in TabSRMM 3]]%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
